text: Reginald Joseph Gibson (10 December 1912 – 26 July 1969) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League (VFL). After his football career he served in the Royal Australian Navy in World War II. == Notes == == External links == * *Reg Gibson's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1912 births Category:1969 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players Category:Sydney Swans players Category:Australian military personnel of World War II
